title: Personal MACOS VMWare image, not much progress yet.
description:
after a hard drive failure my only backup of this virtual machine is on the opposite coast of the country at my dad's house, luck ally he has FIOS so I'm hoping a couple trackers will help me keep a nice steady fast transfer rate. First time I've ever attempted to start a torrent on my own.

Nobody should really have any interest in this but me as its an older version of Mac OS X without many adjustments, I just don't want to restart and redo the research to Linux/BSD-ify it as much as possible. Also iCloud might have a bunch of pictures of my pet Squirrel. He has a Facebook page if you really really want to see him.

I guess I'll find out fairly soon if I can delete a torrent after I've started it... Here goes nothing. =)
